1.title: Episode #8.1

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: The series returns with Michael discovering how learning a new language can help stave off dementia. Giles goes vegan for a month and Alain learns how to protect your teeth from a hidden danger.

2.title: Episode #8.2

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

2.plot: Michael and Zoe test if exercise 'snacking' (short bursts of activity) are as good for you as one long workout. Giles asks how we can get more iron in our diet. Gabriel learns of a breakthrough in gene therapy.

3.title: Episode #8.3

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

3.plot: Can a glass of wine protect your blood cells from the harmful effects of junk food? Do home breathalyser kits work? What is it safe to eat and drink when pregnant?

4.title: Episode #8.4

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

4.plot: Can singing boost feel-good chemicals in the brain? How can music help people with dementia? Is man-flu real? Is detoxing a con? Can group singing help post natal depression?

5.title: Episode #8.5

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

5.plot: Michael discovers what giving up alcohol for a month really does to your health. Gabriel investigates the benefits and risks of medicinal cannabis. How to avoid exam stress.

6.title: Episode #8.6

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

6.plot: Can t'ai chi offer the same health benefits as vigorous exercise? What can we do about heartburn? How safe are the medicines we buy online? Plus revolutionary new brain surgery that is saving lives.

1.title: Episode #1.1

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: Is your BMI the best way to judge fitness? Can tremors be stopped by ultrasound? Should we all take an Aspirin to help us live longer? Michael Mosley is joined by a team of doctors using their expertise to sort out all that conflicting health information that bombards and confuses us every day.

2.title: Episode #1.2

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

2.plot: Are vitamin pills money down the drain? Will antibiotics cure back pain? And does getting cold make you catch one? Does standing at work help your heart rate and glucose level? What to do if someone chokes? Michael Mosley and his team of doctors investigate and give us all some welcome guidance.

3.title: Episode #1.3

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

3.plot: Michael Mosley and the team of doctors test if trees could be the answer to removing air pollution. And they move on to consider if smoothies are good for you? How much caffeine is in common drinks? Do probiotics help digestion? And should more people be taking HRT? Watch and learn!

1.title: Episode #4.1

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: Dr. Saleyha Ahsan examines how we can burn excess fat without any extra effort. Dr. Chris van Tulleken puts protein shakes to the test, while Michael Mosley reveals how to get the benefits from resistance exercise without going down the gym. Surgeon Gabriel Weston questions whether smoothies and juices with antioxidants live up to the hype and she follows the story of a woman who gets her vision back thanks to a bionic eye.

2.title: Episode #4.2

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

2.plot: Dr Chris van Tulleken oversees an experiment to see if you can get healthier not by changing what you eat but when you eat, while Gabriel Weston investigates whether low-sugar products could be making us put on weight. Dr Saleyha Ahsan looks into scented products and what they do to the air in our homes. The team also follows the story of a 12-year-old girl trying out a new treatment for peanut allergy.

3.title: Episode #4.3

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

3.plot: Is olive oil good for us? are beards unhygienic? and is meat really bad for us?

4.title: Episode #4.4

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

4.plot: The doctors reveal the secrets to how we can all stick to those health resolutions we made at New Year, but are already struggling to keep. Surgeon Gabriel Weston experiments with a herbal supplement said to help us drink less alcohol, Dr Chris van Tulleken reveals some unusual ways to get a better night's sleep, and Michael Mosley uncovers the secret of staying motivated. Meanwhile, Dr Saleyha Ahsan tests some revolutionary new science that could help us all easily lose weight and be healthier.

1.title: Episode #7.1

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: In this programme, Michael Mosley finds out why fizzy drinks make you eat more. GP Dr Zoe Williams investigates whether caffeine boosts your physical performance. Geneticist Dr Giles Yeo discovers what men can do about baldness. Surgeon Gabriel Weston looks into the new artificial pancreas that could transform life for diabetics. And Dr Alain Gregoire gives the psychiatrist's guide to obsessive compulsive disorder.

2.title: Episode #7.2

episode of.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor (TV Series 2013– )

2.plot: Michael Mosley runs an experiment to test the claim that coconut oil can cut cholesterol. Giles Yeo investigates how much fruit is too much. Zoe Williams investigates a sleep disorder that causes up to 40,000 road accidents a year. Michael quizzes two experts on whether genetic-testing kits are worth the money. And Alain Gregoire finds out how you can use your eyes to help cope with age-related hearing loss.
